node.text: Adversity is when the best part of every human shows up. For me, I decided the darkness was going to become light and focused on rebuilding communities, one dish at a time. Every day, my team works to keep our business and the future of food moving forward with the help of tools from @Adobe Acrobat. Watch my full story and share with me what drives you forward. https://adobe.ly/Jose-IG #AdobePartner

node.text: where we @WCKitchen are distributing hot meals with Father Luke outside his church here. The water is starting to go down thankfully so more community members are coming back…One step at a time we will get through this! #ChefsForLouisiana

node.title: UPDATE from Lafitte south of New Orleans

node.text: Wanted to give you a behind scenes tour of @WCKitchen headquarters in New Orleans! Meet the WCK team & volunteers cooking & distributing tens of thousands of hot meals in NOLA & hard hit Parishes! @natemook #ChefsForLouisiana

node.text: Adversity is when the best part of every human shows up. For me, I decided the darkness was going to become light and focused on rebuilding communities, one dish at a time. Every day, my team works to keep our business and the future of food moving forward with the help of tools from @Adobe Acrobat. Watch my full story and share with me what drives you forward. https://adobe.ly/Jose-IG #AdobePartner

node.text: This is Malcom & Dwayne! They are longtime friends who both lost their roofs during Ida & their homes are starting to mold...For now they sleep on their porches. No power means no food…so they come to @WCKitchen for a hot meal each day—always with big smiles! #ChefsForLouisiana

node.text: Reporting from our friends AJ’s Produce in New Orleans…no electricity but they jumped in to support! WCK team has been cooking non-stop because no power means no food or shops…We’ve seen many people desperate for a meal…

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by José Andrés on August 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, tree and outdoors.

node.text: Hola from New Orleans! 👋 @WCKitchen team is safe after Hurricane #Ida…But no power here & maybe not for days or more! We already are serving hot pasta, sandwiches, fruit to hungry families…Also just delivered to Emergency Ops Center & cleanup crews in street! #ChefsForLouisiana
